Method Detail

onIPLocationDetermined

void onIPLocationDetermined(Location location)
Called when the AcceleratorClient.requestIPLocation(com.skyhookwireless.accelerator.AcceleratorClient.IPLocationListener) operation determines a location successfully.

If there was an error, then this method will not be called, and the onIPLocationError method will be called instead.

The location is guaranteed to contain the following extra:

  • elapsedRealtimeMillis as long which is the elapsed real-time of fix, in milliseconds since system boot.

    This value can be reliably compared to elapsedRealtime(), to calculate the age of a fix and to compare Location fixes. This is reliable because elapsed real-time is guaranteed monotonic for each system boot and continues to increment even when the system is in deep sleep (unlike getTime()).

The location may contain the following extras:

  • type as IPLocationType which describes the type of the IP address.
  • streetAddress as StreetAddress which holds the street address of the location. The only data member that will be populated for IP locations is the postal code.

Parameters:
location - the location determined from the IP address.

onIPLocationError

void onIPLocationError(int errorCode)
Called when an error occurs when determining location.

This method will be called only if an error occurred. If the location was determined successfully, then the onIPLocationDetermined method will be called instead.

Parameters:
errorCode - the error code of the operation. Possible error code ERROR_UNAUTHORIZED, ERROR_SERVER_UNAVAILABLE, ERROR_CANNOT_DETERMINE_LOCATION. More details can be found in AcceleratorStatusCodes.
